<http://example.org/pt#stmt/14> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.",
        "Despite network name, network does not serve the northernmost stations on the Underground, though network does serve the southernmost station at Morden, the terminus of one of the two southern branches.",
        "Due to conflict between the two Paddington it was not until October 1884 that the inner circle was completed.",
        "History Main articles: History of the Crossrail project, Crossrail, and TfL Rail In 2001, Cross London Rail Links (CLRL), a 50/50 joint-venture between Transport for London (TfL) and the Department for Transport (DfT), was formed to develop and promote the Crossrail scheme,[8] and also a Wimbledon–Hackney scheme, Crossrail 2.",
        "Pancras\", \"Euston Square\", \"Great Portland Street\", \"Baker Street\", \"Finchley Road\", \"Wembley Park\", \"Preston Road\", \"Northwick Park\", \"Harrow-on-the-Hill\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Uxbridge branch\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Harrow-on-the-Hill\", \"West Harrow\", \"Rayners Lane\", \"Eastcote\", \"Ruislip Manor\", \"Ruislip\", \"Ickenham\", \"Hillingdon\", \"Uxbridge\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Amersham / Chesham branch\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Harrow-on-the-Hill\", \"North Harrow\", \"Pinner\", \"Northwood Hills\", \"Northwood\", \"Moor Park\", \"Rickmansworth\", \"Chorleywood\", \"Chalfont & Latimer\", \"Amersham\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Chesham spur\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Chalfont & Latimer\", \"Chesham\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Watford branch\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Harrow-on-the-Hill\", \"North Harrow\", \"Pinner\", \"Northwood Hills\", \"Northwood\", \"Croxley Green\", \"Watford\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Northern line\", \"colour\": \"black\", \"branches\": [ { \"branch\": \"High Barnet branch (north)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"High Barnet\", \"Totteridge & Whetstone\", \"Woodside Park\", \"West Finchley\", \"Finchley Central\", \"East Finchley\", \"Highgate\", \"Archway\", \"Tufnell Park\", \"Kentish Town\", \"Camden Town\", \"Mornington Crescent\", \"Euston\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Edgware branch (north)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Edgware\", \"Burnt Oak\", \"Colindale\", \"Hendon Central\", \"Brent Cross\", \"Golders Green\", \"Hampstead\", \"Belsize Park\", \"Chalk Farm\", \"Camden Town\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Mill Hill East spur\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Finchley Central\", \"Mill Hill East\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Charing Cross branch (central-south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Euston\", \"Warren Street\", \"Goodge Street\", \"Tottenham Court Road\", \"Leicester Square\", \"Charing Cross\", \"Embankment\", \"Waterloo\", \"Kennington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Bank branch (central-south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Euston\", \"King's Cross St.",
        "That was surrounded by the rings of Outer zones 3a, 3b and 3c (all coloured orange on maps).",
