<http://example.org/pt#stmt/142> prov:value "1 October 1868 Opened as Bayswater, renamed Bayswater (Queen's Road) & Westbourne Grove in 1923, Bayswater (Queen's Road) in 1933 and Bayswater (Queensway) in 1946, after which the suffix was gradually dropped.[7] 51°30′43″N 000°11′17″W Paddington Elizabeth line National Rail A pale two storey stone building, with gold coloured letters at the top reading \"METROPOLITAN RAILWAY\" and \"PADDINGTON STATION\", windows on the first floor.",
