<http://example.org/pt#stmt/17> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.",
        "In 2009, the closed loop around the centre of London on the north side of the River Thames was broken at Edgware Road and extended west to become a spiral to Hammersmith.",
        "In the east, routes to Abbey Wood (curtailed from Ebbsfleet to avoid conflicts with the North Kent lines) and Shenfield were selected.",
        "In the north west of the network, on the Metropolitan line, zones 7, 8 and 9 (formerly A - D) cover stations outside Greater London including Amersham and Chesham in Buckinghamshire.",
        "Pancras\", \"Angel\", \"Old Street\", \"Moorgate\", \"Bank\", \"London Bridge\", \"Borough\", \"Elephant & Castle\", \"Kennington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Morden branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Oval\", \"Stockwell\", \"Clapham North\", \"Clapham Common\", \"Clapham South\", \"Balham\", \"Tooting Bec\", \"Tooting Broadway\", \"Colliers Wood\", \"South Wimbledon\", \"Morden\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Battersea branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Nine Elms\", \"Battersea Power Station\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Piccadilly line\", \"colour\": \"dark blue\", \"branches\": [ { \"branch\": \"Main (Cockfosters to Heathrow)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Cockfosters\", \"Oakwood\", \"Southgate\", \"Arnos Grove\", \"Bounds Green\", \"Wood Green\", \"Turnpike Lane\", \"Manor House\", \"Finsbury Park\", \"Arsenal\", \"Holloway Road\", \"Caledonian Road\", \"King's Cross St.",
        "The two main northern branches run south to join at Camden Town where two routes, one via Charing Cross in the West End and the other via Bank in the East, continue and then join at Kennington in Southwark.",
        "These five zones covered all London Underground stations within Greater London.[8] 3a, 3b and 3c were combined into a single Outer zone 3 for London Buses.[8] The off-peak One Day Travelcard, initially launched on 22 April 1984, also used the zones.[9] British Rail stations in London were brought into the fare zones when the weekly, monthly and annual Capitalcard was introduced on 6 January 1985.[10] The fare zones were also used for the off-peak One Day Capitalcard launched in June 1986.[5] When the Capitalcard and Travelcard tickets were folded into a single Travelcard brand on 8 January 1989, the outer zones were renamed." .

<http://example.org/pt#stmt/170> prov:value "All passenger trains were diverted via the Bank branch, with several not stopping at stations until trains were safely on the Bank branch.[98][99] In popular culture In August debut novel Ghostwritten, David Mitchell characterises the Northern line as \"the psycho of the family\".[100] The Bloc Party song \"Waiting For the 7.18\" references the Northern line as \"the loudest\".[101] As part of a series of twelve books tied to the twelve lines of the London Underground, A Northern Line Minute focuses on the Northern line.[102] The New Vaudeville Band's 1967 song \"Finchley Central\" (\"On Tour\" in the US) mentions several stations on the line.[103] The Nick Drake song \"Parasite\" references the Northern Line.[104] The 1982 Robyn Hitchcock song \"Fifty Two Stations\" begins, \"There's fifty-two stations on the Northern Line/None of stations is yours, one of stations is mine.\"[105] The 2021 Maisie Peters song \"Elvis Song\" begins, \"Cold bench on a platform/Last train on the Northern Line.\"[106] Maps ^map 1 High Barnet – 51°39′02″N 000°11′39″W ^map 2 Totteridge & Whetstone – 51°37′50″N 000°10′45″W ^map 3 Woodside Park – 51°37′05″N 000°11′08″W ^map 4 West Finchley – 51°36′34″N 000°11′18″W ^map 5 Mill Hill East – 51°36′30″N 000°12′37″W ^map 6 Finchley Central – 51°36′04″N 000°11′33″W ^map 7 East Finchley – 51°35′14″N 000°09′54″W ^map 8 Highgate – 51°34′40″N 000°08′45″W ^map 9 Archway – 51°33′56″N 000°08′06″W ^map 10 Tufnell Park – 51°33′24″N 000°08′17″W ^map 11 Kentish Town – 51°33′01″N 000°08′26″W ^map 12 Edgware – 51°36′50″N 000°16′30″W ^map 13 Burnt Oak – 51°36′10″N 000°15′50″W ^map 14 Colindale – 51°35′44″N 000°15′00″W ^map 15 Hendon Central – 51°34′59″N 000°13′34″W ^map 16 Brent Cross – 51°34′36″N 000°12′49″W ^map 17 Golders Green – 51°34′19″N 000°11′38″W ^map 18 Hampstead – 51°33′25″N 000°10′42″W ^map 19 Belsize Park – 51°33′01″N 000°09′52″W ^map 20 Chalk Farm – 51°32′39″N 000°09′12″W ^map 21 Camden Town – 51°32′22″