<http://example.org/pt#stmt/2> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"cable-car\" 2 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"coach\" 3 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying false isScheduledService false modeName \"cycle\" 4 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService false modeName \"cycle-hire\" 5 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"dlr\" 6 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"elizabeth-line\" 7 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying false isScheduledService false modeName \"interchange-keep-sitting\" 8 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying false isScheduledService false modeName \"interchange-secure\" 9 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"national-rail\" 10 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"overground\" 11 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"replacement-bus\" 12 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"river-bus\" 13 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"river-tour\" 14 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying false isScheduledService false modeName \"taxi\" 15 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"tram\" 16 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"tube\" 17 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService false isFarePaying false isScheduledService false modeName \"walking\"",
        "Circle line A red S7 Stock train arriving at the clockwise platform at Monument station A Circle line S7 Stock train at Monument Overview Termini Edgware Road Hammersmith Stations 36 Colour on map Corporate Yellow (with black outline until 1990)[1] Website tfl.gov.uk/tube/route/circle/ Edit this at Wikidata Service Type Rapid transit System London Underground Depot(s) Hammersmith Rolling stock S7 Stock Ridership 141.627 million (2019)[a][2] passenger journeys History Opened Infrastructure opened in stages between 1863 (163 years ago) and 1884; shown as a separate line on the Tube map from 1949 Last extension 13 December 2009 Technical Line length 27 km (17 mi) Character Sub-surface Track gauge 1,435 mm (4 ft 8+1⁄2 in) standard gauge Transport for London rail lines The Circle line is a spiral-shaped London Underground line, running from Hammersmith in the west to Edgware Road and then looping around central London back to Edgware Road.",
        "Elizabeth line An Elizabeth line Class 345 train at Reading in January 2026 Overview System National Rail Locale Greater London Berkshire Buckinghamshire Essex Predecessor TfL Rail First service 24 May 2022; 3 years ago Current operator GTS Rail Operations (under concession from TfL)[1] Annual ridership 243 million Increase10% (2024/2025)[2] passenger journeys Website tfl.gov.uk/modes/elizabeth-line/ Edit this at Wikidata Route Termini West: Heathrow Terminal 4, Heathrow Terminal 5 and Reading East: Abbey Wood and Shenfield Stops 41 Distance travelled 117 km (73 mi)[3] Technical Rolling stock Class 345[4] Track gauge 1,435 mm (4 ft 8+1⁄2 in) standard gauge Electrification Overhead line, 25 kV 50 Hz AC Operating speed Core section: 95 km/h (60 mph) GWML, Heathrow and GEML: 145 km/h (90 mph) Track owners Transport for London (Old Oak Common–Abbey Wood and Stratford) Network Rail (Pudding Mill Lane–Shenfield, and Old Oak Common–Reading) Heathrow Airport Holdings (Heathrow branch) Transport for London rail lines The Elizabeth line is a railway line that runs across Greater London and nearby towns.",
        "Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources.",
        "Stations only served by National Rail services are not shown in this map.",
        "TFL API - structured Rules/laws - for transport unstructured https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-on-rail-passengers-rights-and-obligations-regulation-no-13712007/guidance-on-regulation",
        "This article is about the London Underground line.",
        "[0…99] 0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Line, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" Apid \"1\" name \"1\" modeName \"bus\" disruptions [] created \"2026-03-31T11:01:31.293Z\" modified \"2026-03-31T11:01:31.293Z",
        "{ \"network\": \"London Underground\", \"operator\": \"Transport for London\", \"lines\": [ { \"name\": \"Bakerloo line\", \"colour\": \"brown\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Harrow & Wealdstone\", \"Kenton\", \"South Kenton\", \"North Wembley\", \"Wembley Central\", \"Stonebridge Park\", \"Harlesden\", \"Willesden Junction\", \"Kensal Green\", \"Queen's Park\", \"Kilburn Park\", \"Maida Vale\", \"Warwick Avenue\", \"Paddington\", \"Edgware Road\", \"Marylebone\", \"Baker Street\", \"Regent's Park\", \"Oxford Circus\", \"Piccadilly Circus\", \"Charing Cross\", \"Embankment\", \"Waterloo\", \"Lambeth North\", \"Elephant & Castle\" ] }, { \"name\": \"Central line\", \"colour\": \"red\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"West Ruislip\", \"Ruislip Gardens\", \"South Ruislip\", \"Northolt\", \"Greenford\", \"Perivale\", \"Hanger Lane\", \"North Acton\", \"East Acton\", \"White City\", \"Shepherd's Bush\", \"Holland Park\", \"Notting Hill Gate\", \"Queensway\", \"Lancaster Gate\", \"Marble Arch\", \"Bond Street\", \"Oxford Circus\", \"Tottenham Court Road\", \"Holborn\", \"Chancery Lane\", \"St Paul's\", \"Bank\", \"Liverpool Street\", \"Bethnal Green\", \"Mile End\", \"Stratford\", \"Leyton\", \"Leytonstone\", \"Wanstead\", \"Redbridge\", \"Gants Hill\", \"Newbury Park\", \"Barkingside\", \"Fairlop\", \"Hainault\", \"Chigwell\", \"Roding Valley\", \"Woodford\", \"South Woodford\", \"Snaresbrook\", \"Ealing Broadway\", \"West Acton\" ], \"note\": \"Branches at Leytonstone (Hainault loop) and at North Acton (Ealing Broadway branch)\" }, { \"name\": \"Circle line\", \"colour\": \"yellow\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Hammersmith\", \"Goldhawk Road\", \"Shepherd's Bush Market\", \"Wood Lane\", \"Latimer Road\", \"Ladbroke Grove\", \"Westbourne Park\", \"Royal Oak\", \"Paddington\", \"Edgware Road\", \"Baker Street\", \"Great Portland Street\", \"Euston Square\", \"King's Cross St." .

<http://example.org/pt#stmt/20> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.",
        "Each of five outer zones forms a concentric ring around area.",
        "For most of Merton length the Northern line is a deep tube line.[a] The portion between Stockwell and Borough opened in 1890 and is the oldest section of deep-level tube line on the network.",
        "Pancras\", \"Angel\", \"Old Street\", \"Moorgate\", \"Bank\", \"London Bridge\", \"Borough\", \"Elephant & Castle\", \"Kennington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Morden branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Oval\", \"Stockwell\", \"Clapham North\", \"Clapham Common\", \"Clapham South\", \"Balham\", \"Tooting Bec\", \"Tooting Broadway\", \"Colliers Wood\", \"South Wimbledon\", \"Morden\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Battersea branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Nine Elms\", \"Battersea Power Station\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Piccadilly line\", \"colour\": \"dark blue\", \"branches\": [ { \"branch\": \"Main (Cockfosters to Heathrow)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Cockfosters\", \"Oakwood\", \"Southgate\", \"Arnos Grove\", \"Bounds Green\", \"Wood Green\", \"Turnpike Lane\", \"Manor House\", \"Finsbury Park\", \"Arsenal\", \"Holloway Road\", \"Caledonian Road\", \"King's Cross St.",
        "Ten stations in east London, many in the London Borough of Newham area, are in both zone 2 and 3: Abbey Rd, Bromley-by-Bow, Canning Town, East India, Pudding Mill Lane, Star Lane, Stratford, Stratford High Street, Stratford International and West Ham.",
        "The six-car C Stock trains were replaced from 2012 to 2014 by new seven-car S Stock trains.",
        "This committed TfL and the DfT to financing the project, then projected to cost £15.9 billion, with further contributions from Network Rail, BAA,[15] and the City of London.[16] Construction Main article: Crossrail Construction of Crossrail at Tottenham Court Road in September 2011 Work began on 15 May 2009, when piling works started at the future Canary Wharf station.[17] Boring of the railway tunnels was officially completed in June 2015.[18] Installation of the track was completed in September 2017.[19] The European Train Control System (ETCS) signalling was scheduled to be tested in the Heathrow tunnels over the winter of 2017–2018.[20] At the end of August 2018, four months before the scheduled opening of the core section of the line, it was announced that completion was delayed and that the line would not open before autumn 2019.[21] After multiple delays, in August 2020 Crossrail announced that the central section would be ready to open \"in the first half of 2022\".[22] In May 2021, trial running commenced.[23] On 17 May 2022, the line was officially opened by Queen Elizabeth II in honour of commenced.[23 Platinum Jubilee." .

