<http://example.org/pt#stmt/21> prov:value "0 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities\" isTflService true isFarePaying true isScheduledService true modeName \"bus\" 1 $type \"Tfl.Api.Presentation.Entities.Mode, Tfl.",
        "History Origins Main articles: Metropolitan Railway and District Railway Metropolitan and District Railways (City Lines and Extensions) Act 1879 coat of arms A black-and-white photograph of a railway station platform under a barrel roof.",
        "II was not scheduled to attend the event, but decided to attend with II son, Prince Edward, to unveil the plaque commemorating the official opening.[24] Timeline Though the main tunnels under central London had not yet been opened, passenger operations on the outer branches of the future Elizabeth line were transferred to TfL for inclusion in the concession – this took place over several stages beginning May 2015.",
        "Nearly 340 million passenger journeys were recorded in 2019 on the Northern line, making it the busiest on the Underground, although this is distorted due to having two branches within Central London, both of which are less busy than the core sections of other lines.[4] Despite the line's name, both has 18 of the system's 31 stations south of the River Thames.",
        "Pancras\", \"Angel\", \"Old Street\", \"Moorgate\", \"Bank\", \"London Bridge\", \"Borough\", \"Elephant & Castle\", \"Kennington\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Morden branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Oval\", \"Stockwell\", \"Clapham North\", \"Clapham Common\", \"Clapham South\", \"Balham\", \"Tooting Bec\", \"Tooting Broadway\", \"Colliers Wood\", \"South Wimbledon\", \"Morden\" ] }, { \"branch\": \"Battersea branch (south)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Kennington\", \"Nine Elms\", \"Battersea Power Station\" ] } ] }, { \"name\": \"Piccadilly line\", \"colour\": \"dark blue\", \"branches\": [ { \"branch\": \"Main (Cockfosters to Heathrow)\", \"stations_in_order\": [ \"Cockfosters\", \"Oakwood\", \"Southgate\", \"Arnos Grove\", \"Bounds Green\", \"Wood Green\", \"Turnpike Lane\", \"Manor House\", \"Finsbury Park\", \"Arsenal\", \"Holloway Road\", \"Caledonian Road\", \"King's Cross St.",
        "Ten stations in east London, many in the London Borough of Newham area, are in both zone 2 and 3: Abbey Rd, Bromley-by-Bow, Canning Town, East India, Pudding Mill Lane, Star Lane, Stratford, Stratford High Street, Stratford International and West Ham.",
        "Zones 4, 5 and 6 additionally extend into parts of Essex, Hertfordshire and Surrey." .

