<http://example.org/pt#stmt/42> prov:value "At the start of the 20th century, the District and Metropolitan were seeing increased competition in central London from the new electric underground tube lines and trams, and conversion to electric traction was seen as the way forward.[10] Experiments were carried out on the Earl's Court to High Street Kensington section, and a jointly owned six-carriage train began passenger service in 1900.",
