<http://example.org/pt#stmt/87> prov:value "51°31′12″N 000°10′04″W Baker Street A street filled with people in front of a light grey building that has variously coloured signs protruding from building stating a variety of different things 10 January 1863 Connects with Bakerloo, Jubilee and Metropolitan lines.",
        "Monday-Sunday Capping is distinct from an Oyster 7-day Travelcard in that the latter may be purchased on any day of the week, whereas Monday-Sunday Capping \"lapses\" at the start of the travel day on Monday.",
